
** Installation of Cortex itself

1. Change directory into the CORTEX_release_ directory (we will call this the root directory).
2. cd gsl-1.15/
3. Type

make clean
./configure --prefix=/path/to/Cortex_release_v1.0.whatever/gsl-1.15/user_install
make
make install

3. Change directory back to the root directory.
4. Open the Makefile with a text editor, and change this text

-L/full/path/to/your/install/of/CORTEX_release_v1.0.5.10/gsl-1.15 -L/full/path/to/your/install/of/CORTEX_release_v1.0.5.10/gsl-1.15/gsl -L/full/path/to/your/install/of/CORTEX_release_v1.0.5.10/gsl-1.15/user_install

so that the three instances of 
/full/path/to/your/install/of/
are replaced with the appropriate path for your install

5. Type 
make cortex_var

If this fails, consult the manual at : http://cortexassembler.sourceforge.net/cortex_var_user_manual.pdf




** Other packages/set-up required for run_calls.pl and for dumping VCFs

1. Obtain Stampy from 
   http://www.well.ox.ac.uk/project-stampy
   Unzip it somewhere, cd into it and type make. 
   Stampy requirements: Stampy needs Python version 2.6 or 2.7
                        Only supports x86_64 and (experimental) Mac.
   The run_calls.pl and process_calls.pl will need to know where stampy.py is (I pass the path in as an argument)


2. Add 
   /path/to/CORTEX_release_v_whatever/scripts/analyse_variants/bioinf-perl/lib/
   and
   /path/to/CORTEX_release_v_whatever/scripts/calling/
   to your PERL5LIB

3. Add /path/to/CORTEX_release_v_whatever/scripts/analyse_variants/needleman_wunsch-0.3.0/ to your PATH

4. cd scripts/analyse_variants/needleman_wunsch-0.3.0/
   make clean
   make

